Installation Instructions
-------------------------

Linux terminal: $ cat * > "Ubuntu 17.10.zip"
Windows 10 PowerShell: $ cmd /c copy /b * "Ubuntu 17.10.zip"

Unzip "Ubuntu 17.10.zip," and open "Ubuntu 17.10.vmx" in VMware Workstation 15 Player.
If one sees a login prompt, simply restart the virtual machine.

Double-click on ``Default Project.osp'' on the desktop.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Optional

To verify the authenticity of "Ubuntu 17.10.zip":
$ gpg --keyserver hkps://keyserver.ubuntu.com:443 --recv-keys 0x4191f431
$ gpg --verify SHA1SUMS.gpg SHA1SUMS (example)

To verify the integrity of "Ubuntu 17.10.zip":
Linux terminal: $ sha1sum "Ubuntu 17.10.zip" (example)
Windows 10 PowerShell: $ Get-FileHash "Ubuntu 17.10.zip" -Algorithm SHA1 (example)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Caveats:
OpenShot 1.4.3 is unstable, so save the project frequently.
The image does not provide root access. If one needs root access, feel free to replicate the image (see below).






[How the Image Was Created]

Downloaded the base operating system:
ubuntu-17.10-desktop-amd64.iso
(source: http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/releases/17.10/)

VMware Workstation 15 Player:
Created a new virtual machine entitled "Ubuntu 17.10" using Easy Install
Memory: 4 GB, Processors: 2, Virtualize Intel VT-x/EPT

Modifications/changes:
1)  updated /etc/apt/sources.list with the latest server URL, and updated package lists
2)  installed OpenShot and GStreamer Libav plug-in
3)  upgraded all packages
4)  enabled automatic login
5)  disabled automatic screen lock
6)  removed the lock screen button from the status menu
7)  set up the project directory
8)  bookmarked the project directory in Nautilus
9)  created a shortcut to the project directory on the desktop
10) added Terminal and OpenShot to Favorites
11) streamlined the Dash
12) selected ``never'' to notify me when a new Ubuntu version is available
  
How to perform the modifications/changes:
1)  $ sudo sed -i -re 's/([a-z]{2}\.)?archive.ubuntu.com|security.ubuntu.com/old-releases.ubuntu.com/g' /etc/apt/sources.list && sudo apt update
2)  $ sudo apt install openshot gstreamer1.0-libav
3)  $ sudo apt upgrade
4)  Settings > Details > Users > Automatic Login: ON
5)  Settings > Privacy > Screen Lock > Automatic Screen Lock: OFF
6)  $ dconf write /org/gnome/desktop/lockdown/disable-user-switching true
7)  See ``'How to Use App' Video'' README, steps (2) and (3).
8)  Click on, and drag, the ``introduction'' folder to left panel onto ``New bookmark.''
9)  Nautilus > Preferences > Behavior: select ``Show action to create symbolic links''
        Right-click on ``Default Project.osp,'' and select ``Create Link.''
        Click on, and drag, the link to the desktop.
10) Open each application; in the Dash right-click on the application; and select ``Add to Favorites.''
11) For each application, in the Dash right-click on the application and select ``Remove from Favorites.''
12) Software Updater > Settings > Notify me of a new Ubuntu version: Never

Sent "Ubuntu 17.10.vmdk" and "Ubuntu 17.10.vmx" to a compressed folder entitled "Ubuntu 17.10.zip"